00162 int
00163 cuddSymmCheck(
00164   DdManager * table,
00165   int  x,
00166   int  y)
00167 {
00168     DdNode *f,*f0,*f1,*f01,*f00,*f11,*f10;
00169     int comple;         /* f0 is complemented */
00170     int xsymmy;         /* x and y may be positively symmetric */
00171     int xsymmyp;        /* x and y may be negatively symmetric */
00172     int arccount;       /* number of arcs from layer x to layer y */
00173     int TotalRefCount;  /* total reference count of layer y minus 1 */
00174     int yindex;
00175     int i;
00176 #ifdef __osf__
00177 #pragma pointer_size save
00178 #pragma pointer_size short
00179 #endif
00180     DdNode **list;
00181 #ifdef __osf__
00182 #pragma pointer_size restore
00183 #endif
00184     int slots;
00185 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00186     int xindex;
00187 #endif
00188 
00189 
00190     /* Checks that x and y are not the projection functions.
00191     ** For x it is sufficient to check whether there is only one
00192     ** node; indeed, if there is one node, it is the projection function
00193     ** and it cannot point to y. Hence, if y isn't just the projection
00194     ** function, it has one arc coming from a layer different from x.
00195     */
00196     if (table->subtables[x].keys == 1) {
00197         return(0);
00198     }
00199     yindex = table->invperm[y];
00200     if (table->subtables[y].keys == 1) {
00201         if (table->vars[yindex]->ref == 1)
00202             return(0);
00203     }
00204 
00205     xsymmy = xsymmyp = 1;
00206     arccount = 0;
00207     slots = table->subtables[x].slots;
00208     list = table->subtables[x].nodelist;
00209     for (i = 0; i < slots; i++) {
00210         f = list[i];
00211         while (f != NULL) {
00212             /* Find f1, f0, f11, f10, f01, f00. */
00213             f1 = cuddT(f);
00214             f0 = Cudd_Regular(cuddE(f));
00215             comple = Cudd_IsComplement(cuddE(f));
00216             if ((int) f1->index == yindex) {
00217                 arccount++;
00218                 f11 = cuddT(f1); f10 = cuddE(f1);
00219             } else {
00220                 if ((int) f0->index != yindex) {
00221                     /* If f is an isolated projection function it is
00222                     ** allowed to bypass layer y.
00223                     */
00224                     if (f1 != DD_ONE(table) || f0 != DD_ONE(table) || f->ref != 1)
00225                         return(0); /* f bypasses layer y */
00226                 }
00227                 f11 = f10 = f1;
00228             }
00229             if ((int) f0->index == yindex) {
00230                 arccount++;
00231                 f01 = cuddT(f0); f00 = cuddE(f0);
00232             } else {
00233                 f01 = f00 = f0;
00234             }
00235             if (comple) {
00236                 f01 = Cudd_Not(f01);
00237                 f00 = Cudd_Not(f00);
00238             }
00239 
00240             if (f1 != DD_ONE(table) || f0 != DD_ONE(table) || f->ref != 1) {
00241                 xsymmy &= f01 == f10;
00242                 xsymmyp &= f11 == f00;
00243                 if ((xsymmy == 0) && (xsymmyp == 0))
00244                     return(0);
00245             }
00246 
00247             f = f->next;
00248         } /* while */
00249     } /* for */
00250 
00251     /* Calculate the total reference counts of y */
00252     TotalRefCount = -1; /* -1 for projection function */
00253     slots = table->subtables[y].slots;
00254     list = table->subtables[y].nodelist;
00255     for (i = 0; i < slots; i++) {
00256         f = list[i];
00257         while (f != NULL) {
00258             TotalRefCount += f->ref;
00259             f = f->next;
00260         }
00261     }
00262 
00263 #if defined(DD_DEBUG) && defined(DD_VERBOSE)
00264     if (arccount == TotalRefCount) {
00265         xindex = table->invperm[x];
00266         (void) fprintf(stdout,"Found symmetry! x =%d\ty = %d\tPos(%d,%d)\n",
00267             xindex,yindex,x,y);
00268     }
00269 #endif
00270 
00271     return(arccount == TotalRefCount);
00272 
00273 } /* end of cuddSymmCheck */

00329 
00330     for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
00331         x = table->perm[i];

00337

00340         table->subtables[i].next = i;

00356                 (void) fprintf(stdout,"-");

00358                        table->isolated) {
00359                 (void) fprintf(stdout,"+"); /* should never happen */

00364 #endif

00367

00375     (void) fprintf(stdout,"#:G_SIFTING %8d: symmetric groups",symgroups);
00376 #endif
00377 
00378     return(1+symvars);
00379

00413 int
00414 cuddSymmSiftingConv(

00418 {
00419     int         i;
00420     int         *var;
00421     int         size;
00422     int         x;
00423     int         result;
00424     int         symvars;
00425     int         symgroups;
00426     int         classes;
00427     int         initialSize;
00428 #ifdef DD_STATS
00429     int         previousSize;
00430 #endif
00431 
00432     initialSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00433 
00434     size = table->size;
00435 
00436     /* Find order in which to sift variables. */
00437     var = NULL;
00438     entry = ALLOC(int,size);
00439     if (entry == NULL) {
00440         table->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
00441         goto ddSymmSiftingConvOutOfMem;
00442     }
00443     var = ALLOC(int,size);
00444     if (var == NULL) {
00445         table->errorCode = CUDD_MEMORY_OUT;
00446         goto ddSymmSiftingConvOutOfMem;
00447     }
00448 
00449     for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
00450         x = table->perm[i];
00451         entry[i] = table->subtables[x].keys;
00452         var[i] = i;
00453     }
00454 
00455     qsort((void *)var,size,sizeof(int),(int (*)(const void *, const void *))ddSymmUniqueCompare);
00456 
00457     /* Initialize the symmetry of each subtable to itself
00458     ** for first pass of converging symmetric sifting.
00459     */
00460     for (i = lower; i <= upper; i++) {
00461         table->subtables[i].next = i;
00462     }
00463 
00464     for (i = 0; i < ddMin(table->siftMaxVar, table->size); i++) {
00465         if (ddTotalNumberSwapping >= table->siftMaxSwap)
00466             break;
00467         x = table->perm[var[i]];
00468         if (x < lower || x > upper) continue;
00469         /* Only sift if not in symmetry group already. */
00470         if (table->subtables[x].next == (unsigned) x) {
00471 #ifdef DD_STATS
00472             previousSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00473 #endif
00474             result = ddSymmSiftingAux(table,x,lower,upper);
00475             if (!result) goto ddSymmSiftingConvOutOfMem;
00476 #ifdef DD_STATS
00477             if (table->keys < (unsigned) previousSize + table->isolated) {
00478                 (void) fprintf(stdout,"-");
00479             } else if (table->keys > (unsigned) previousSize +
00480                        table->isolated) {
00481                 (void) fprintf(stdout,"+");
00482             } else {
00483                 (void) fprintf(stdout,"=");
00484             }
00485             fflush(stdout);
00486 #endif
00487         }
00488     }
00489 
00490     /* Sifting now until convergence. */
00491     while ((unsigned) initialSize > table->keys - table->isolated) {
00492         initialSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00493 #ifdef DD_STATS
00494         (void) fprintf(stdout,"\n");
00495 #endif
00496         /* Here we consider only one representative for each symmetry class. */
00497         for (x = lower, classes = 0; x <= upper; x++, classes++) {
00498             while ((unsigned) x < table->subtables[x].next) {
00499                 x = table->subtables[x].next;
00500             }
00501             /* Here x is the largest index in a group.
00502             ** Groups consist of adjacent variables.
00503             ** Hence, the next increment of x will move it to a new group.
00504             */
00505             i = table->invperm[x];
00506             entry[i] = table->subtables[x].keys;
00507             var[classes] = i;
00508         }
00509 
00510         qsort((void *)var,classes,sizeof(int),(int (*)(const void *, const void *))ddSymmUniqueCompare);
00511 
00512         /* Now sift. */
00513         for (i = 0; i < ddMin(table->siftMaxVar,classes); i++) {
00514             if (ddTotalNumberSwapping >= table->siftMaxSwap)
00515                 break;
00516             x = table->perm[var[i]];
00517             if ((unsigned) x >= table->subtables[x].next) {
00518 #ifdef DD_STATS
00519                 previousSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00520 #endif
00521                 result = ddSymmSiftingConvAux(table,x,lower,upper);
00522                 if (!result ) goto ddSymmSiftingConvOutOfMem;
00523 #ifdef DD_STATS
00524                 if (table->keys < (unsigned) previousSize + table->isolated) {
00525                     (void) fprintf(stdout,"-");
00526                 } else if (table->keys > (unsigned) previousSize +
00527                            table->isolated) {
00528                     (void) fprintf(stdout,"+");
00529                 } else {
00530                     (void) fprintf(stdout,"=");
00531                 }
00532                 fflush(stdout);
00533 #endif
00534             }
00535         } /* for */
00536     }
00537 
00538     ddSymmSummary(table, lower, upper, &symvars, &symgroups);
00539 
00540 #ifdef DD_STATS
00541     (void) fprintf(stdout,"\n#:S_SIFTING %8d: symmetric variables\n",symvars);
00542     (void) fprintf(stdout,"#:G_SIFTING %8d: symmetric groups",symgroups);
00543 #endif
00544 
00545     FREE(var);
00546     FREE(entry);
00547 
00548     return(1+symvars);
00549 
00550 ddSymmSiftingConvOutOfMem:
00551 
00552     if (entry != NULL) FREE(entry);
00553     if (var != NULL) FREE(var);
00554 
00555     return(0);
00556 
00557 } /* end of cuddSymmSiftingConv */

00605 static int
00606 ddSymmSiftingAux(
00607   DdManager * table,
00608   int  x,
00609   int  xLow,
00610   int  xHigh)
00611 {
00612     Move *move;
00613     Move *moveUp;       /* list of up moves */
00614     Move *moveDown;     /* list of down moves */
00615     int  initialSize;
00616     int  result;
00617     int  i;
00618     int  topbot;        /* index to either top or bottom of symmetry group */
00619     int  initGroupSize, finalGroupSize;
00620 
00621 
00622 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00623     /* check for previously detected symmetry */
00624     assert(table->subtables[x].next == (unsigned) x);
00625 #endif
00626 
00627     initialSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00628 
00629     moveDown = NULL;
00630     moveUp = NULL;
00631 
00632     if ((x - xLow) > (xHigh - x)) {
00633         /* Will go down first, unless x == xHigh:
00634         ** Look for consecutive symmetries above x.
00635         */
00636         for (i = x; i > xLow; i--) {
00637             if (!cuddSymmCheck(table,i-1,i))
00638                 break;
00639             topbot = table->subtables[i-1].next; /* find top of i-1's group */
00640             table->subtables[i-1].next = i;
00641             table->subtables[x].next = topbot; /* x is bottom of group so its */
00642                                                /* next is top of i-1's group */
00643             i = topbot + 1; /* add 1 for i--; new i is top of symm group */
00644         }
00645     } else {
00646         /* Will go up first unless x == xlow:
00647         ** Look for consecutive symmetries below x.
00648         */
00649         for (i = x; i < xHigh; i++) {
00650             if (!cuddSymmCheck(table,i,i+1))
00651                 break;
00652             /* find bottom of i+1's symm group */
00653             topbot = i + 1;
00654             while ((unsigned) topbot < table->subtables[topbot].next) {
00655                 topbot = table->subtables[topbot].next;
00656             }
00657             table->subtables[topbot].next = table->subtables[i].next;
00658             table->subtables[i].next = i + 1;
00659             i = topbot - 1; /* subtract 1 for i++; new i is bottom of group */
00660         }
00661     }
00662 
00663     /* Now x may be in the middle of a symmetry group.
00664     ** Find bottom of x's symm group.
00665     */
00666     while ((unsigned) x < table->subtables[x].next)
00667         x = table->subtables[x].next;
00668 
00669     if (x == xLow) { /* Sift down */
00670 
00671 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00672         /* x must be a singleton */
00673         assert((unsigned) x == table->subtables[x].next);
00674 #endif
00675         if (x == xHigh) return(1);      /* just one variable */
00676 
00677         initGroupSize = 1;
00678 
00679         moveDown = ddSymmSiftingDown(table,x,xHigh);
00680             /* after this point x --> xHigh, unless early term */
00681         if (moveDown == MV_OOM) goto ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem;
00682         if (moveDown == NULL) return(1);
00683 
00684         x = moveDown->y;
00685         /* Find bottom of x's group */
00686         i = x;
00687         while ((unsigned) i < table->subtables[i].next) {
00688             i = table->subtables[i].next;
00689         }
00690 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00691         /* x should be the top of the symmetry group and i the bottom */
00692         assert((unsigned) i >= table->subtables[i].next);
00693         assert((unsigned) x == table->subtables[i].next);
00694 #endif
00695         finalGroupSize = i - x + 1;
00696 
00697         if (initGroupSize == finalGroupSize) {
00698             /* No new symmetry groups detected, return to best position */
00699             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveDown,initialSize);
00700         } else {
00701             initialSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00702             moveUp = ddSymmSiftingUp(table,x,xLow);
00703             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveUp,initialSize);
00704         }
00705         if (!result) goto ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem;
00706 
00707     } else if (cuddNextHigh(table,x) > xHigh) { /* Sift up */
00708         /* Find top of x's symm group */
00709         i = x;                          /* bottom */
00710         x = table->subtables[x].next;   /* top */
00711 
00712         if (x == xLow) return(1); /* just one big group */
00713 
00714         initGroupSize = i - x + 1;
00715 
00716         moveUp = ddSymmSiftingUp(table,x,xLow);
00717             /* after this point x --> xLow, unless early term */
00718         if (moveUp == MV_OOM) goto ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem;
00719         if (moveUp == NULL) return(1);
00720 
00721         x = moveUp->x;
00722         /* Find top of x's group */
00723         i = table->subtables[x].next;
00724 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00725         /* x should be the bottom of the symmetry group and i the top */
00726         assert((unsigned) x >= table->subtables[x].next);
00727         assert((unsigned) i == table->subtables[x].next);
00728 #endif
00729         finalGroupSize = x - i + 1;
00730 
00731         if (initGroupSize == finalGroupSize) {
00732             /* No new symmetry groups detected, return to best position */
00733             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveUp,initialSize);
00734         } else {
00735             initialSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00736             moveDown = ddSymmSiftingDown(table,x,xHigh);
00737             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveDown,initialSize);
00738         }
00739         if (!result) goto ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem;
00740 
00741     } else if ((x - xLow) > (xHigh - x)) { /* must go down first: shorter */
00742 
00743         moveDown = ddSymmSiftingDown(table,x,xHigh);
00744             /* at this point x == xHigh, unless early term */
00745         if (moveDown == MV_OOM) goto ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem;
00746 
00747         if (moveDown != NULL) {
00748             x = moveDown->y;    /* x is top here */
00749             i = x;
00750             while ((unsigned) i < table->subtables[i].next) {
00751                 i = table->subtables[i].next;
00752             }
00753         } else {
00754             i = x;
00755             while ((unsigned) i < table->subtables[i].next) {
00756                 i = table->subtables[i].next;
00757             }
00758             x = table->subtables[i].next;
00759         }
00760 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00761         /* x should be the top of the symmetry group and i the bottom */
00762         assert((unsigned) i >= table->subtables[i].next);
00763         assert((unsigned) x == table->subtables[i].next);
00764 #endif
00765         initGroupSize = i - x + 1;
00766 
00767         moveUp = ddSymmSiftingUp(table,x,xLow);
00768         if (moveUp == MV_OOM) goto ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem;
00769 
00770         if (moveUp != NULL) {
00771             x = moveUp->x;
00772             i = table->subtables[x].next;
00773         } else {
00774             i = x;
00775             while ((unsigned) x < table->subtables[x].next)
00776                 x = table->subtables[x].next;
00777         }
00778 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00779         /* x should be the bottom of the symmetry group and i the top */
00780         assert((unsigned) x >= table->subtables[x].next);
00781         assert((unsigned) i == table->subtables[x].next);
00782 #endif
00783         finalGroupSize = x - i + 1;
00784 
00785         if (initGroupSize == finalGroupSize) {
00786             /* No new symmetry groups detected, return to best position */
00787             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveUp,initialSize);
00788         } else {
00789             while (moveDown != NULL) {
00790                 move = moveDown->next;
00791                 cuddDeallocNode(table, (DdNode *) moveDown);
00792                 moveDown = move;
00793             }
00794             initialSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00795             moveDown = ddSymmSiftingDown(table,x,xHigh);
00796             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveDown,initialSize);
00797         }
00798         if (!result) goto ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem;
00799 
00800     } else { /* moving up first: shorter */
00801         /* Find top of x's symmetry group */
00802         x = table->subtables[x].next;
00803 
00804         moveUp = ddSymmSiftingUp(table,x,xLow);
00805             /* at this point x == xHigh, unless early term */
00806         if (moveUp == MV_OOM) goto ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem;
00807 
00808         if (moveUp != NULL) {
00809             x = moveUp->x;
00810             i = table->subtables[x].next;
00811         } else {
00812             while ((unsigned) x < table->subtables[x].next)
00813                 x = table->subtables[x].next;
00814             i = table->subtables[x].next;
00815         }
00816 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00817         /* x is bottom of the symmetry group and i is top */
00818         assert((unsigned) x >= table->subtables[x].next);
00819         assert((unsigned) i == table->subtables[x].next);
00820 #endif
00821         initGroupSize = x - i + 1;
00822 
00823         moveDown = ddSymmSiftingDown(table,x,xHigh);
00824         if (moveDown == MV_OOM) goto ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem;
00825 
00826         if (moveDown != NULL) {
00827             x = moveDown->y;
00828             i = x;
00829             while ((unsigned) i < table->subtables[i].next) {
00830                 i = table->subtables[i].next;
00831             }
00832         } else {
00833             i = x;
00834             x = table->subtables[x].next;
00835         }
00836 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00837         /* x should be the top of the symmetry group and i the bottom */
00838         assert((unsigned) i >= table->subtables[i].next);
00839         assert((unsigned) x == table->subtables[i].next);
00840 #endif
00841         finalGroupSize = i - x + 1;
00842 
00843         if (initGroupSize == finalGroupSize) {
00844             /* No new symmetries detected, go back to best position */
00845             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveDown,initialSize);
00846         } else {
00847             while (moveUp != NULL) {
00848                 move = moveUp->next;
00849                 cuddDeallocNode(table, (DdNode *) moveUp);
00850                 moveUp = move;
00851             }
00852             initialSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00853             moveUp = ddSymmSiftingUp(table,x,xLow);
00854             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveUp,initialSize);
00855         }
00856         if (!result) goto ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem;
00857     }
00858 
00859     while (moveDown != NULL) {
00860         move = moveDown->next;
00861         cuddDeallocNode(table, (DdNode *) moveDown);
00862         moveDown = move;
00863     }
00864     while (moveUp != NULL) {
00865         move = moveUp->next;
00866         cuddDeallocNode(table, (DdNode *) moveUp);
00867         moveUp = move;
00868     }
00869 
00870     return(1);
00871 
00872 ddSymmSiftingAuxOutOfMem:
00873     while (moveDown != NULL) {
00874         move = moveDown->next;
00875         cuddDeallocNode(table, (DdNode *) moveDown);
00876         moveDown = move;
00877     }
00878     while (moveUp != NULL) {
00879         move = moveUp->next;
00880         cuddDeallocNode(table, (DdNode *) moveUp);
00881         moveUp = move;
00882     }
00883 
00884     return(0);
00885 
00886 } /* end of ddSymmSiftingAux */

00903 static int
00904 ddSymmSiftingConvAux(
00905   DdManager * table,
00906   int  x,
00907   int  xLow,
00908   int  xHigh)
00909 {
00910     Move *move;
00911     Move *moveUp;       /* list of up moves */
00912     Move *moveDown;     /* list of down moves */
00913     int  initialSize;
00914     int  result;
00915     int  i;
00916     int  initGroupSize, finalGroupSize;
00917 
00918 
00919     initialSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00920 
00921     moveDown = NULL;
00922     moveUp = NULL;
00923 
00924     if (x == xLow) { /* Sift down */
00925 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00926         /* x is bottom of symmetry group */
00927         assert((unsigned) x >= table->subtables[x].next);
00928 #endif
00929         i = table->subtables[x].next;
00930         initGroupSize = x - i + 1;
00931 
00932         moveDown = ddSymmSiftingDown(table,x,xHigh);
00933             /* at this point x == xHigh, unless early term */
00934         if (moveDown == MV_OOM) goto ddSymmSiftingConvAuxOutOfMem;
00935         if (moveDown == NULL) return(1);
00936 
00937         x = moveDown->y;
00938         i = x;
00939         while ((unsigned) i < table->subtables[i].next) {
00940             i = table->subtables[i].next;
00941         }
00942 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00943         /* x should be the top of the symmetric group and i the bottom */
00944         assert((unsigned) i >= table->subtables[i].next);
00945         assert((unsigned) x == table->subtables[i].next);
00946 #endif
00947         finalGroupSize = i - x + 1;
00948 
00949         if (initGroupSize == finalGroupSize) {
00950             /* No new symmetries detected, go back to best position */
00951             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveDown,initialSize);
00952         } else {
00953             initialSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00954             moveUp = ddSymmSiftingUp(table,x,xLow);
00955             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveUp,initialSize);
00956         }
00957         if (!result) goto ddSymmSiftingConvAuxOutOfMem;
00958 
00959     } else if (cuddNextHigh(table,x) > xHigh) { /* Sift up */
00960         /* Find top of x's symm group */
00961         while ((unsigned) x < table->subtables[x].next)
00962             x = table->subtables[x].next;

00964         x = table->subtables[x].next;   /* top */
00965

00970         moveUp = ddSymmSiftingUp(table,x,xLow);
00971             /* at this point x == xLow, unless early term */
00972         if (moveUp == MV_OOM) goto ddSymmSiftingConvAuxOutOfMem;
00973         if (moveUp == NULL) return(1);
00974 
00975         x = moveUp->x;
00976         i = table->subtables[x].next;
00977 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
00978         /* x should be the bottom of the symmetry group and i the top */
00979         assert((unsigned) x >= table->subtables[x].next);
00980         assert((unsigned) i == table->subtables[x].next);
00981 #endif

00983

00985             /* No new symmetry groups detected, return to best position */
00986             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveUp,initialSize);
00987         } else {
00988             initialSize = table->keys - table->isolated;
00989             moveDown = ddSymmSiftingDown(table,x,xHigh);
00990             result = ddSymmSiftingBackward(table,moveDown,initialSize);
00991         }
00992         if (!result)
00993             goto ddSymmSiftingConvAuxOutOfMem;
00994 
00995     } else if ((x - xLow) > (xHigh - x)) { /* must go down first: shorter */

00997             /* at this point x == xHigh, unless early term */
00998         if (moveDown == MV_OOM) goto ddSymmSiftingConvAuxOutOfMem;
00999 
01000         if (moveDown != NULL) {
01001             x = moveDown->y;
01002             i = x;
01003             while ((unsigned) i < table->subtables[i].next) {
01004                 i = table->subtables[i].next;
01005             }
01006         } else {
01007             while ((unsigned) x < table->subtables[x].next)
01008                 x = table->subtables[x].next;
01009             i = x;
01010             x = table->subtables[x].next;
01011         }
01012 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01013         /* x should be the top of the symmetry group and i the bottom */
01014         assert((unsigned) i >= table->subtables[i].next);
01015         assert((unsigned) x == table->subtables[i].next);
01016 #endif
01017         initGroupSize = i - x + 1;
01018 
01019         moveUp = ddSymmSiftingUp(table,x,xLow);
01020         if (moveUp == MV_OOM) goto ddSymmSiftingConvAuxOutOfMem;
01021 
01022         if (moveUp != NULL) {
01023             x = moveUp->x;
01024             i = table->subtables[x].next;
01025         } else {
01026             i = x;
01027             while ((unsigned) x < table->subtables[x].next)
01028                 x = table->subtables[x].next;

01030 #ifdef DD_DEBUG

01063         } else {

01066                 x = table->subtables[x].next;

01092 #endif

01140 
01156 static Move *
01157 ddSymmSiftingUp(
01158   DdManager * table,
01159   int  y,
01160   int  xLow)
01161 {
01162     Move *moves;
01163     Move *move;
01164     int  x;
01165     int  size;
01166     int  i;
01167     int  gxtop,gybot;
01168     int  limitSize;
01169     int  xindex, yindex;
01170     int  zindex;
01171     int  z;
01172     int  isolated;
01173     int  L;     /* lower bound on DD size */
01174 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01175     int  checkL;
01176 #endif
01177 
01178 
01179     moves = NULL;
01180     yindex = table->invperm[y];
01181 
01182     /* Initialize the lower bound.
01183     ** The part of the DD below the bottom of y' group will not change.
01184     ** The part of the DD above y that does not interact with y will not
01185     ** change. The rest may vanish in the best case, except for
01186     ** the nodes at level xLow, which will not vanish, regardless.
01187     */
01188     limitSize = L = table->keys - table->isolated;
01189     gybot = y;
01190     while ((unsigned) gybot < table->subtables[gybot].next)
01191         gybot = table->subtables[gybot].next;
01192     for (z = xLow + 1; z <= gybot; z++) {
01193         zindex = table->invperm[z];
01194         if (zindex == yindex || cuddTestInteract(table,zindex,yindex)) {
01195             isolated = table->vars[zindex]->ref == 1;
01196             L -= table->subtables[z].keys - isolated;
01197         }
01198     }
01199 
01200     x = cuddNextLow(table,y);
01201     while (x >= xLow && L <= limitSize) {
01202 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01203         gybot = y;
01204         while ((unsigned) gybot < table->subtables[gybot].next)
01205             gybot = table->subtables[gybot].next;
01206         checkL = table->keys - table->isolated;
01207         for (z = xLow + 1; z <= gybot; z++) {
01208             zindex = table->invperm[z];
01209             if (zindex == yindex || cuddTestInteract(table,zindex,yindex)) {
01210                 isolated = table->vars[zindex]->ref == 1;
01211                 checkL -= table->subtables[z].keys - isolated;
01212             }
01213         }
01214         assert(L == checkL);
01215 #endif
01216         gxtop = table->subtables[x].next;
01217         if (cuddSymmCheck(table,x,y)) {
01218             /* Symmetry found, attach symm groups */
01219             table->subtables[x].next = y;
01220             i = table->subtables[y].next;
01221             while (table->subtables[i].next != (unsigned) y)
01222                 i = table->subtables[i].next;
01223             table->subtables[i].next = gxtop;
01224         } else if (table->subtables[x].next == (unsigned) x &&
01225                    table->subtables[y].next == (unsigned) y) {
01226             /* x and y have self symmetry */
01227             xindex = table->invperm[x];
01228             size = cuddSwapInPlace(table,x,y);
01229 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01230             assert(table->subtables[x].next == (unsigned) x);
01231             assert(table->subtables[y].next == (unsigned) y);
01232 #endif
01233             if (size == 0) goto ddSymmSiftingUpOutOfMem;
01234             /* Update the lower bound. */
01235             if (cuddTestInteract(table,xindex,yindex)) {
01236                 isolated = table->vars[xindex]->ref == 1;
01237                 L += table->subtables[y].keys - isolated;
01238             }
01239             move = (Move *) cuddDynamicAllocNode(table);
01240             if (move == NULL) goto ddSymmSiftingUpOutOfMem;
01241             move->x = x;
01242             move->y = y;
01243             move->size = size;
01244             move->next = moves;
01245             moves = move;
01246             if ((double) size > (double) limitSize * table->maxGrowth)
01247                 return(moves);
01248             if (size < limitSize) limitSize = size;
01249         } else { /* Group move */
01250             size = ddSymmGroupMove(table,x,y,&moves);
01251             if (size == 0) goto ddSymmSiftingUpOutOfMem;
01252             /* Update the lower bound. */
01253             z = moves->y;
01254             do {
01255                 zindex = table->invperm[z];
01256                 if (cuddTestInteract(table,zindex,yindex)) {
01257                     isolated = table->vars[zindex]->ref == 1;
01258                     L += table->subtables[z].keys - isolated;
01259                 }
01260                 z = table->subtables[z].next;
01261             } while (z != (int) moves->y);
01262             if ((double) size > (double) limitSize * table->maxGrowth)
01263                 return(moves);
01264             if (size < limitSize) limitSize = size;
01265         }
01266         y = gxtop;
01267         x = cuddNextLow(table,y);
01268     }
01269 
01270     return(moves);
01271 
01272 ddSymmSiftingUpOutOfMem:
01273     while (moves != NULL) {
01274         move = moves->next;
01275         cuddDeallocNode(table, (DdNode *) moves);
01276         moves = move;
01277     }
01278     return(MV_OOM);
01279 
01280 } /* end of ddSymmSiftingUp */

01282 
01298 static Move *
01299 ddSymmSiftingDown(
01300   DdManager * table,
01301   int  x,
01302   int  xHigh)
01303 {
01304     Move *moves;
01305     Move *move;
01306     int  y;
01307     int  size;
01308     int  limitSize;
01309     int  gxtop,gybot;
01310     int  R;     /* upper bound on node decrease */
01311     int  xindex, yindex;
01312     int  isolated;
01313     int  z;
01314     int  zindex;
01315 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01316     int  checkR;
01317 #endif
01318 
01319     moves = NULL;
01320     /* Initialize R */
01321     xindex = table->invperm[x];
01322     gxtop = table->subtables[x].next;
01323     limitSize = size = table->keys - table->isolated;
01324     R = 0;
01325     for (z = xHigh; z > gxtop; z--) {
01326         zindex = table->invperm[z];
01327         if (zindex == xindex || cuddTestInteract(table,xindex,zindex)) {
01328             isolated = table->vars[zindex]->ref == 1;
01329             R += table->subtables[z].keys - isolated;
01330         }
01331     }
01332 
01333     y = cuddNextHigh(table,x);
01334     while (y <= xHigh && size - R < limitSize) {
01335 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01336         gxtop = table->subtables[x].next;
01337         checkR = 0;
01338         for (z = xHigh; z > gxtop; z--) {
01339             zindex = table->invperm[z];
01340             if (zindex == xindex || cuddTestInteract(table,xindex,zindex)) {
01341                 isolated = table->vars[zindex]->ref == 1;
01342                 checkR += table->subtables[z].keys - isolated;
01343             }
01344         }
01345         assert(R == checkR);
01346 #endif
01347         gybot = table->subtables[y].next;
01348         while (table->subtables[gybot].next != (unsigned) y)
01349             gybot = table->subtables[gybot].next;
01350         if (cuddSymmCheck(table,x,y)) {
01351             /* Symmetry found, attach symm groups */
01352             gxtop = table->subtables[x].next;
01353             table->subtables[x].next = y;
01354             table->subtables[gybot].next = gxtop;
01355         } else if (table->subtables[x].next == (unsigned) x &&
01356                    table->subtables[y].next == (unsigned) y) {
01357             /* x and y have self symmetry */
01358             /* Update upper bound on node decrease. */
01359             yindex = table->invperm[y];
01360             if (cuddTestInteract(table,xindex,yindex)) {
01361                 isolated = table->vars[yindex]->ref == 1;
01362                 R -= table->subtables[y].keys - isolated;
01363             }
01364             size = cuddSwapInPlace(table,x,y);
01365 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01366             assert(table->subtables[x].next == (unsigned) x);
01367             assert(table->subtables[y].next == (unsigned) y);
01368 #endif
01369             if (size == 0) goto ddSymmSiftingDownOutOfMem;
01370             move = (Move *) cuddDynamicAllocNode(table);
01371             if (move == NULL) goto ddSymmSiftingDownOutOfMem;
01372             move->x = x;
01373             move->y = y;
01374             move->size = size;
01375             move->next = moves;
01376             moves = move;
01377             if ((double) size > (double) limitSize * table->maxGrowth)
01378                 return(moves);
01379             if (size < limitSize) limitSize = size;
01380         } else { /* Group move */
01381             /* Update upper bound on node decrease: first phase. */
01382             gxtop = table->subtables[x].next;
01383             z = gxtop + 1;
01384             do {
01385                 zindex = table->invperm[z];
01386                 if (zindex == xindex || cuddTestInteract(table,xindex,zindex)) {
01387                     isolated = table->vars[zindex]->ref == 1;
01388                     R -= table->subtables[z].keys - isolated;
01389                 }
01390                 z++;
01391             } while (z <= gybot);
01392             size = ddSymmGroupMove(table,x,y,&moves);
01393             if (size == 0) goto ddSymmSiftingDownOutOfMem;
01394             if ((double) size > (double) limitSize * table->maxGrowth)
01395                 return(moves);
01396             if (size < limitSize) limitSize = size;
01397             /* Update upper bound on node decrease: second phase. */
01398             gxtop = table->subtables[gybot].next;
01399             for (z = gxtop + 1; z <= gybot; z++) {
01400                 zindex = table->invperm[z];
01401                 if (zindex == xindex || cuddTestInteract(table,xindex,zindex)) {
01402                     isolated = table->vars[zindex]->ref == 1;
01403                     R += table->subtables[z].keys - isolated;
01404                 }
01405             }
01406         }
01407         x = gybot;
01408         y = cuddNextHigh(table,x);
01409     }
01410 
01411     return(moves);
01412 
01413 ddSymmSiftingDownOutOfMem:
01414     while (moves != NULL) {
01415         move = moves->next;
01416         cuddDeallocNode(table, (DdNode *) moves);
01417         moves = move;
01418     }
01419     return(MV_OOM);
01420 
01421 } /* end of ddSymmSiftingDown */

01423 
01436 static int
01437 ddSymmGroupMove(
01438   DdManager * table,
01439   int  x,
01440   int  y,
01441   Move ** moves)
01442 {
01443     Move *move;
01444     int  size = 0;
01445     int  i,j;
01446     int  xtop,xbot,xsize,ytop,ybot,ysize,newxtop;
01447     int  swapx = 0, swapy = 0;
01448 
01449 #if DD_DEBUG
01450     assert(x < y);      /* we assume that x < y */
01451 #endif
01452     /* Find top, bottom, and size for the two groups. */
01453     xbot = x;
01454     xtop = table->subtables[x].next;
01455     xsize = xbot - xtop + 1;
01456     ybot = y;
01457     while ((unsigned) ybot < table->subtables[ybot].next)
01458         ybot = table->subtables[ybot].next;
01459     ytop = y;
01460     ysize = ybot - ytop + 1;
01461 
01462     /* Sift the variables of the second group up through the first group. */
01463     for (i = 1; i <= ysize; i++) {
01464         for (j = 1; j <= xsize; j++) {
01465             size = cuddSwapInPlace(table,x,y);
01466             if (size == 0) return(0);
01467             swapx = x; swapy = y;
01468             y = x;
01469             x = y - 1;
01470         }
01471         y = ytop + i;
01472         x = y - 1;
01473     }
01474 
01475     /* fix symmetries */
01476     y = xtop; /* ytop is now where xtop used to be */
01477     for (i = 0; i < ysize-1 ; i++) {
01478         table->subtables[y].next = y + 1;
01479         y = y + 1;
01480     }
01481     table->subtables[y].next = xtop; /* y is bottom of its group, join */
01482                                      /* its symmetry to top of its group */
01483     x = y + 1;
01484     newxtop = x;
01485     for (i = 0; i < xsize - 1 ; i++) {
01486         table->subtables[x].next = x + 1;
01487         x = x + 1;
01488     }
01489     table->subtables[x].next = newxtop; /* x is bottom of its group, join */
01490                                         /* its symmetry to top of its group */
01491     /* Store group move */
01492     move = (Move *) cuddDynamicAllocNode(table);
01493     if (move == NULL) return(0);
01494     move->x = swapx;
01495     move->y = swapy;
01496     move->size = size;
01497     move->next = *moves;
01498     *moves = move;
01499 
01500     return(size);
01501 
01502 } /* end of ddSymmGroupMove */

01588 static int
01589 ddSymmSiftingBackward(
01590   DdManager * table,
01591   Move * moves,
01592   int  size)
01593 {
01594     Move *move;
01595     int  res;
01596 
01597     for (move = moves; move != NULL; move = move->next) {
01598         if (move->size < size) {
01599             size = move->size;
01600         }
01601     }
01602 
01603     for (move = moves; move != NULL; move = move->next) {
01604         if (move->size == size) return(1);
01605         if (table->subtables[move->x].next == move->x && table->subtables[move->y].next == move->y) {
01606             res = cuddSwapInPlace(table,(int)move->x,(int)move->y);
01607 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01608             assert(table->subtables[move->x].next == move->x);
01609             assert(table->subtables[move->y].next == move->y);
01610 #endif
01611         } else { /* Group move necessary */
01612             res = ddSymmGroupMoveBackward(table,(int)move->x,(int)move->y);
01613         }
01614         if (!res) return(0);
01615     }
01616 
01617     return(1);
01618 
01619 } /* end of ddSymmSiftingBackward */

01632 static void
01633 ddSymmSummary(
01634   DdManager * table,
01635   int  lower,
01636   int  upper,
01637   int * symvars,
01638   int * symgroups)
01639 {
01640     int i,x,gbot;
01641     int TotalSymm = 0;
01642     int TotalSymmGroups = 0;
01643 
01644     for (i = lower; i <= upper; i++) {
01645         if (table->subtables[i].next != (unsigned) i) {
01646             TotalSymmGroups++;
01647             x = i;
01648             do {
01649                 TotalSymm++;
01650                 gbot = x;
01651                 x = table->subtables[x].next;
01652             } while (x != i);
01653 #ifdef DD_DEBUG
01654             assert(table->subtables[gbot].next == (unsigned) i);
01655 #endif
01656             i = gbot;
01657         }
01658     }
01659     *symvars = TotalSymm;
01660     *symgroups = TotalSymmGroups;
01661 
01662     return;
01663 
01664 } /* end of ddSymmSummary */
